pr_title: Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard page Milestone-1.1
pr_body: ## Overview 1. This PR is for [Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard page project](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ii3MXnA5gFaueLDnMYugnPo9zIdgjRjHLAJO3pn3ZoU/edit?usp=sharing) [Milestone 1.1] 2. This PR does the following: Adds topics and stories to the Learner Dashboard page. ## Essential Checklist - [x] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".) - [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine. - [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.) - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you. - [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop". ## Proof that changes are correct One-off job: ## PR Pointers - Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change). - Oppiabot will notify you when you don't add a PR_CHANGELOG label. If you are unable to do so, please @-mention a code owner (who will be in the Reviewers list), or ask on [Gitter](https://gitter.im/oppia/oppia-chat). - For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers). - Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays. - Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed. - Oppiabot can assign anyone for review/help if you leave a comment like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL" - Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

pr_title: Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard Page Milestone-1.3
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR is for [Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard page project](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ii3MXnA5gFaueLDnMYugnPo9zIdgjRjHLAJO3pn3ZoU/edit?usp=sharing) [Milestone 1.3]
2. This PR does the following: Adds Edit Goals tab in the Learner Dashboard page. **This page will not be displayed to the user until Milestone 2.3.**

## Essential Checklist

- [x] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct
[Web view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1DCXphGQPPpEPxW7faO7EaJDGVbBRJEiY/view?usp=sharing)
[Mobile view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1G9y8DzkJ9D2fKg38EXg1yfeVRiUr-mdT/view?usp=sharing)
[Tablet view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1usluBdxJi3P1BoAEETkIFThXrSNiTHT5/view?usp=sharing)

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- Oppiabot will notify you when you don't add a PR_CHANGELOG label. If you are unable to do so, please @-mention a code owner (who will be in the Reviewers list), or ask on [Gitter](https://gitter.im/oppia/oppia-chat).
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Oppiabot can assign anyone for review/help if you leave a comment like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL"
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

pr_title: Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard Page Milestone-1.4
pr_body: ## Overview 1. This PR is for [Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard page project](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ii3MXnA5gFaueLDnMYugnPo9zIdgjRjHLAJO3pn3ZoU/edit?usp=sharing) [Milestone 1.4] 2. This PR does the following: Adds Community Lessons tab in the Learner Dashboard. **This page will not be displayed to the user until Milestone 2.3.** ## Essential Checklist - [x] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".) - [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine. - [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.) - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you. - [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop". ## Proof that changes are correct [Web view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1XzjLfhPdTpSJJR-6lpLX_j0bqmpga5TC/view?usp=sharing) [Mobile view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MOaDnKfkZEcB11m43zkONY6e22VD2aWk/view?usp=sharing) [Tablet view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1T3DdhsMlkthQ1YGneaBM4qrCxs50XLiI/view?usp=sharing) For Subscriptions: 1. Web view 2. Mobile view 3. Tablet view ## PR Pointers - Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change). - Oppiabot will notify you when you don't add a PR_CHANGELOG label. If you are unable to do so, please @-mention a code owner (who will be in the Reviewers list), or ask on [Gitter](https://gitter.im/oppia/oppia-chat). - For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers). - Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays. - Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed. - Oppiabot can assign anyone for review/help if you leave a comment like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL" - Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

pr_title: Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard Page Milestone-1.5
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR is for [Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard page project](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ii3MXnA5gFaueLDnMYugnPo9zIdgjRjHLAJO3pn3ZoU/edit?usp=sharing) [Milestone 1.5]
2. This PR does the following: Adds Progress tab in the Learner Dashboard. **This page will not be displayed to the user until Milestone 2.3.**

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [ ] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [ ] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [ ] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct
[Web view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jUi2qPY_pvi21OblJqh0XWJ4aYpNAXPL/view?usp=sharing)
[Mobile view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1qwWOBkexTGm5fo3eNrSJQ_EX3O9-Q_HM/view?usp=sharing)
[Tablet view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1AqbJOEoxvh3FweVv6PfLuJVjXtBqam3n/view?usp=sharing)

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- Oppiabot will notify you when you don't add a PR_CHANGELOG label. If you are unable to do so, please @-mention a code owner (who will be in the Reviewers list), or ask on [Gitter](https://gitter.im/oppia/oppia-chat).
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Oppiabot can assign anyone for review/help if you leave a comment like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL"
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

pr_title: Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard Page Milestone-2.1
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR is for [Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard page project](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ii3MXnA5gFaueLDnMYugnPo9zIdgjRjHLAJO3pn3ZoU/edit?usp=sharing) [Milestone 2.1]
2. This PR does the following: Adds Skill Proficiency section in the Progress tab of Learner Dashboard. **This page will not be displayed to the user until Milestone 2.3.**

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [ ] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [ ] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [ ] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

[Web view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ArrpJQflFxPQ6ZKL8PnIGED0R6hBm6FB/view?usp=sharing)
[Tablet view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1DUF_qc7uxsDqB3qtQBlyKxzNF4RB6rgZ/view?usp=sharing)
[Mobile view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/13p86ZhOhgFkktjiHvoE2V8q5Se6gdMJH/view?usp=sharing) | [Updated Mobile view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1c97GOD-ncP8nnLdH1IUzySOP-dLJgxkh/view?usp=sharing)

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes made in this PR work correctly.
If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}".
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- Oppiabot will notify you when you don't add a PR_CHANGELOG label. If you are unable to do so, please @-mention a code owner (who will be in the Reviewers list), or ask on [Gitter](https://gitter.im/oppia/oppia-chat).
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Oppiabot can assign anyone for review/help if you leave a comment like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL"
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

pr_title: Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard Page Milestone-2.2
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR is for [Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard page project](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ii3MXnA5gFaueLDnMYugnPo9zIdgjRjHLAJO3pn3ZoU/edit?usp=sharing) [Milestone 2.2]
2. This PR does the following: Adds Home tab in the Learner Dashboard. **This page will not be displayed to the user until Milestone 2.3.**

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [ ] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [ ] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [ ] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

[Web view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1z6U20K97tIKphBMDmY3U7KDSLeDt6yi4/view?usp=sharing)
[Tablet view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jcQlHuverWdhQoZNObsrNxqqGSjMDWVa/view?usp=sharing)
[Mobile view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/10tJTrlySW_K-INUvSmER6LO8ARin_zzi/view?usp=sharing)

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- Oppiabot will notify you when you don't add a PR_CHANGELOG label. If you are unable to do so, please @-mention a code owner (who will be in the Reviewers list), or ask on [Gitter](https://gitter.im/oppia/oppia-chat).
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Oppiabot can assign anyone for review/help if you leave a comment like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL"
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

pr_title: Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard Page Milestone-2.3
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR is for [Redesigning and Updating the Learner Dashboard page project](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ii3MXnA5gFaueLDnMYugnPo9zIdgjRjHLAJO3pn3ZoU/edit?usp=sharing) [Milestone 2.3]
2. This PR does the following: Updates the Learner Dashboard page to display new tabs and removes old ones.

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [ ] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [ ] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [ ] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

[Web view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1VjQJx_xE1n5ip_1eiflFWrJSg3P2p00e/view?usp=sharing)
[Tablet view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1gwxEGvO5HBivmK_3yPjI17S7nato9Gi8/view?usp=sharing)
[Mobile view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1P9WvhgYkbfwvJFUri91MVMsQerBSzzao/view?usp=sharing)

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes made in this PR work correctly.
If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}".
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- Oppiabot will notify you when you don't add a PR_CHANGELOG label. If you are unable to do so, please @-mention a code owner (who will be in the Reviewers list), or ask on [Gitter](https://gitter.im/oppia/oppia-chat).
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Oppiabot can assign anyone for review/help if you leave a comment like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL"
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).
